    "name": "Cantina Sociale",
    "profile": "[b]Cantina Sociale[/b], from Asti/Alba region south of Turin, formed in 1996 with the aim of developing the sound of the alternative Bands of the Seventies by adding personal research, as well as an original theatrical approach, to their progressive rock. The meeting with [a914711], producer and keyboardist of [a1030927], was the beginning of an important artistic path that led to the release of “[u]Balene[/u] (c'è qualcosa di più)” [1] in 2002, for which [b]Cantina Sociale[/b] won the [u]Memorial Demetrio Stratos Prize[/u] in 2003. Tracks from this early album appeared on some compilations. In 2004, the Band participated at the [u]Kalevala Project[/u]. In 2006, the Band published the Live DVD, “[u]Catturati[/u]” [2]. The Band's second album, “[u]Cum Lux[/u]” [3], would release in 2009. After the further third studio release of “[u]Caosfera[/u]“ [4][Digi-Pack] in 2017 which contains seven nice instrumental songs, within 2018 [a3355294] came back as a lead singer of the Band. During 201",
